I adored the first three eps, loved two following ones and okay with the...
body:
Killing Eve: full season = 8 eps swallowed in one day

I adored the first three eps, loved two following ones and okay with the last three eps. I’d prefer there were no last three eps but okay, I can live with that.

Im waiting for the second season anyway even though have no idea what should happen there to make the main relationship intense and complicated again coz rn nevertheless what happened in the last scene it looks quiet resolved. But Im looking forward to find out if they can surprise me

summary:
Having rattled through 6 episodes of Killing Eve today, I can 
categorically say that I’m at least 50% gayer, and I have become...
body:
Having rattled through 6 episodes of Killing Eve today, I can categorically say that I’m at least 50% gayer, and I have become so because of:

Sandra Oh’s hair

Jodie Comer’s face

And Fiona Shaw in power dresses and a fur hat

(why there isn’t a gif set of Fiona Shaw in that hat is a mystery to me)

Anyway - I’m 5% gayer having made this set, best stop before I start shooting rainbows out my eyes.
